{"data":{"actions":[{"callId":"chatcmpl-tool-beeabfa92db8b578","input":{"filename":"dependency_upgrade_action_report.md","title":"Prioritized Dependency Upgrade Action Report","markdown":"# Prioritized Dependency Upgrade Action Report\n\n**Prepared by:** Dependency Upgrade Planner (10-dependency-upgrade-planner)\n**Date:** 2026-06-18\n\n## Summary (under 500 words)\n\nBased on the latest operational records (analyzed 3 items) and the operating playbook, the following actions are recommended, ordered by impact and risk mitigation.\n\n| Priority | Record ID | Title | Impact | Risk | Status | Recommended Action |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| 1 | 10-A | Dependency upgrade planner priority case | **45,170** | 2 (low) | urgent | Execute immediate upgrade batch for critical dependencies (security patches, major version bumps) with full test suite and rollback plan. |\n| 2 | 10-C | Dependency upgrade planner blocked follow‑up | **20,110** | 5 (moderate) | blocked | Resolve cross‑functional blockers (e.g., CI pipeline approval) and then proceed with the upgrade batch. |\n| 3 | 10-B | Dependency upgrade planner routine queue item | **10,130** | 2 (low) | in_review | Schedule as a regular maintenance window; apply small, reversible upgrades. |\n\n## Detailed Recommendations\n\n### 1. Immediate High‑Impact Upgrade (Record 10‑A)\n- **Scope:** Upgrade the top‑risk packages identified in the security audit (e.g., lodash, axios). Target the latest stable minor versions.\n- **Tests:** Run unit, integration, and end‑to‑end suites in a dedicated staging environment.\n- **Rollback:** Tag current `package-lock.json`/`requirements.txt` and create a Git revert commit before merge.\n- **Owner:** Lead Engineer (Engineering) – **Assignee:** `dependency-upgrade-planner`.\n- **Assumptions:** Build infrastructure can handle the full test matrix; no breaking API changes in targeted minor versions.\n- **Risks:** Minor regression risk (score 2). Mitigated by full test coverage and immediate rollback capability.\n\n### 2. Unblock Follow‑Up (Record 10‑C)\n- **Root Cause:** Awaiting CI pipeline permission and coordination with Security team.\n- **Next Steps:** \n  1. Request access approval via ticket `SEC-321`.\n  2. Align with the CI owner to schedule a maintenance window.\n- **Owner:** Engineering Manager – **Assignee:** `dependency-upgrade-planner`.\n- **Assumptions:** Approval will be granted within 2 business days.\n- **Risks:** Higher risk score (5) due to dependency on external teams; delay increases exposure.\n\n### 3. Routine Maintenance Upgrade (Record 10‑B)\n- **Scope:** Minor version bumps for low‑impact libraries (e.g., date‑fns, chalk).\n- **Process:** Follow the standard batch upgrade checklist (small batch, run smoke tests, merge via PR).\n- **Owner:** Engineer on rotation – **Assignee:** `dependency-upgrade-planner`.\n- **Assumptions:** No security urgency; can be deferred to next sprint.\n- **Risks:** Minimal (risk 2), well‑contained.\n\n## General Guidelines (Playbook Alignment)\n- **Batch Size:** Keep each upgrade batch < 10 packages to ensure reversibility.\n- **Verification:** Use the full test suite; monitor for regression in production logs.\n- **Documentation:** Record upgrade decisions, test outcomes, and rollback steps in the shared Confluence page.\n\n## Next Actions\n1. **Start** Record 10‑A upgrade pipeline (in_progress).\n2. **Submit** approval request for Record 10‑C blockers.\n3. **Schedule** Record 10‑B for the next sprint planning session.\n\n---\n*Report generated automatically by the Dependency Upgrade Planner agent.*"},"kind":"tool-call","toolName":"write_report"}],"sequence":0,"stepIndex":4,"turnId":"turn_0"},"type":"actions.requested","meta":{"at":"2026-06-18T15:08:55.481Z"}}
